Reasoning: The paper deals with the characterization of the asymptotic behavior of information and estimation theoretic quantities in coherent fading channels, which is a topic that falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The use of the Mellin transform method for the asymptotic expansion of integrals suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and mathematical software (cs.MS). The optimization of the constrained capacity of a bank of parallel independent coherent fading channels driven by arbitrary discrete inputs may also involve the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which could be relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
